items.name: Advanced Cluster Management for Kubernetes
items.description: Red Hat Advanced Cluster Management for Kubernetes provides the multicluster hub, a central  management console for managing multiple Kubernetes-based clusters across data centers, public clouds, and private clouds.
items.label: api.openshift.com/addon-advanced-cluster-management

items.name: Cluster Logging Operator
items.description: Enable log forwarding to AWS CloudWatch on your cluster for (optionally): application logs (from regular pods), infrastructure logs (from system pods and node logs), and/or audit logs (special node logs with legal/security implications)
items.label: api.openshift.com/addon-cluster-logging-operator

items.name: Use AWS CloudWatch
items.description: Select this if you want to use AWS CloudWatch

items.name: Collect Applications logs
items.description: Let the operator to collect application logs (everything that is deployed not in the `openshift-*` namespaces)

items.name: Collect Infrastructure logs
items.description: Let the operator to collect logs from openshift and kubernetes pods and some nodes

items.name: Collect Audit logs
items.description: Let the operator to collect node logs related to security audits

items.name: CloudWatch region
items.description: AWS region for CloudWatch. Leave empty to set to the cluster region. Example: us-west-1

items.name: [DEPRECATED] Red Hat CodeReady Workspaces
items.description: Installation of the Red Hat CodeReady Workspaces as an add-on service in OpenShift Dedicated and Red Hat OpenShift Service on AWS (ROSA) is deprecated. Bug fixes and support are provided through the end of the 2.15 life cycle. After which, no new feature enhancements are made. You can install Red Hat CodeReady Workspaces on these platforms by using OperatorHub instead.

items.name: Red Hat OpenShift Database Access
items.description: Red Hat OpenShift Database Access makes it easy to discover, connect, deploy, and monitor apps that use cloud hosted databases. This is a Service Preview release. It contains features that are early in development.  Service Preview releases are not production ready and may have features and functionality that are not fully tested. You are advised not to use OpenShift Database Access for production or business-critical workloads.

items.name: Red Hat Openshift API Management
items.description: Install and configure the OpenShift API Management service.
items.label: api.openshift.com/addon-managed-api-service

items.name: ROSA CLI Required
items.description: IMPORTANT: Do not proceed with the RHOAM addon installation from the OCM UI. Recommended installation is via the ROSA CLI. The required AWS roles will not be auto-created if the addon is installed through the OCM UI: [https://access.redhat.com/documentation/en-us/red_hat_openshift_api_management/1/topic/05b07729-c891-4846-8044-aeff49bbfb72]

items.name: CIDR range
items.description: Required: Enter a CIDR block value or apply the default by clicking the link. IMPORTANT: You cannot modify the CIDR block value after installation.

items.name: Notification email
items.description: Enter one or more email addresses for API usage alerts, separated by a space.

items.name: Quota
items.description: Please choose a Quota from the list. IMPORTANT: changes to the configuration will update the configuration of the installation and reduce their rate limit.

items.name: Addon Resource Requirements
items.description: IMPORTANT: Before proceeding, please ensure the target cluster has sufficient resources to support the add-on install. Resource requirements are available from the Product Service Definition document: [https://access.redhat.com/articles/5534341]

items.name: 3scale custom wildcard domain name
items.description: Optional: Enter a custom domain name for 3scale components. IMPORTANT: You cannot modify the domain name after installation.

items.name: Custom SMTP From Address
items.description: Optional: A default SMTP server is provided by default. Add outgoing email address if a custom smtp server is required.

items.name: Custom SMTP Mail Server Address
items.description: Optional: A default SMTP server is provided by default. Add remote mail server address if a custom smtp server is required.

items.name: Custom SMTP Username
items.description: Optional: A default SMTP server is provided by default. Add username if a custom smtp server is required

items.name: Custom SMTP Password [Optional]
items.description: Optional: A default SMTP server is provided by default. Add mail server password if custom smtp is required.

items.name: Custom SMTP Port
items.description: Optional: A default SMTP server is provided by default. Add mail server port if custom smtp is required.

error_msgs: This addon requires more cpu compute capacity than is currently achievable by this cluster. Current max available is 6 vCPUs, but require at least 11 vCPUs. Scale up the number of compute nodes and try again.
